From: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Subject: sched: mark SCHED_HRTICK broken
Date: Wed, 28 Jan 2009 16:46:24 +0100

SCHED_HRTICK is broken and not yet fixed in mainline. WTF is it still
enabled in -rt ?

Tested-by: Carsten Emde <C.Emde@osadl.org>
Signed-off-by: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
---
 kernel/Kconfig.hz |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/features/rt/kernel/Kconfig.hz b/kernel/Kconfig.hz
index 94fabd5..8c8ceb5 100644
--- a/kernel/Kconfig.hz
+++ b/kernel/Kconfig.hz
@@ -55,4 +55,4 @@ config HZ
 	default 1000 if HZ_1000
 
 config SCHED_HRTICK
-	def_bool HIGH_RES_TIMERS && (!SMP || USE_GENERIC_SMP_HELPERS)
+	def_bool HIGH_RES_TIMERS && (!SMP || USE_GENERIC_SMP_HELPERS) && BROKEN
